04/05/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W Bush has invited the foreign ministers of NATO's seven newest members to the White House on Thursday (8 May).
He will deliver a speech to the top diplomats of Bulgaria, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia in the presence of Senate leaders.
The Senate is debating the NATO accession agreement of the seven new members and is expected to ratify it shortly.
White House spokesman Scott McClellan praised the countries' "strong support in the war on terrorism, and in bringing peace and democracy to Afghanistan and Iraq".
(Reuters, AFP - 02/05/03)
